remarks:        ---------------------------------------------------------
remarks:        BGP Communities
remarks:        ---------------------------------------------------------
remarks:        
remarks:        ==== Community added when recieve announces from peers:
remarks:        == IXs
remarks:        59947:210 - routes from DE-CIX (DE)
remarks:        59947:220 - routes from AMS-IX (NL)
remarks:        59947:240 - routes from HE at AMS-IX (NL)
remarks:        59947:260 - routes from Equinix IX (PL)
remarks:        == Customers
remarks:        59947:400 - routes from LL-IX peers all
remarks:        59947:410 - routes from LL-IX peers NL
remarks:        59947:420 - routes from LL-IX peers PL
remarks:        
remarks:        ==== Community accepted from recieved announces:
remarks:        == To peers
remarks:        0:<peer-as> - Deny announcing a route to the peer with <peer-as>
remarks:        59947:<peer-as> - Permit announcing a route to the peer with <peer-as>
remarks:        Permit community has more "weight" rather than deny community
remarks:        
remarks:        1:<peer-as> one prepend to <peer-as>
remarks:        2:<peer-as> two prepends to <peer-as>
remarks:        3:<peer-as> three prepends to <peer-as>
remarks:        
remarks:        0:59947 - Deny announcing a prefix to anybody
remarks:        59947:59947 (or none) - Announce prefix to all peers
remarks:        59947:666 - blackhole trafic to the announced prefix
remarks:        
remarks:        == To Internet Exchanges
remarks:        59947:6521X - announce to DE-CIX
remarks:        59947:6522X - announce to AMS-IX
remarks:        59947:6524X - announce to HE-IX
remarks:        59947:6526X - announce to Equinix IX
remarks:        
remarks:        X = 9 - do not advertise
remarks:        X = [1 .. 5] - add prepend X times
remarks:        
remarks:        Example: If you dont want announce prefix to DE-CIX add community 59947:65219
remarks:        
remarks:        == DE-CIX
